"{\"uid\": \"dailyadvertiser.com.au-story-8768140-cars-collided-on-olympic-highway-uranquinty-teenager-seriously-injured-at-wallendbeen\", \"text\": \"Your digital subscription includes access to content from all our websites in your region.\\r Access unlimited content and the digital versions of our print editions - Today's Paper.  A baby and infant were taken to hospital after a crash outside Wagga on Wednesday afternoon, while a teenager was airlifted after she was seriously injured in a separate crash on Thursday morning.  Loginor signup to continue reading  Emergency services were called to the Olympic Highway at the Dunns Road turn-off at Uranquinty about 4.30pm on Wednesday following reports of a two-car crash.  A spokesperson for NSW Ambulance said paramedics assessed five patients at the scene including two infants.  The infants were a young girl and a baby and they were both taken to Wagga Base Hospital.  Meanwhile, a teenager has sustained serious injuries in a crash on the Olympic Highway near Wallendbeen where she was airlifted to hospital.  Emergency services were called to the scene at about 7.30am on Thursday.  A spokesperson for NSW Ambulance said paramedics responded to the high-speed single vehicle crash where they assessed a teenage girl at the scene who sustained serious injuries.  She was airlifted to Canberra Hospital.  Daily  Today's top stories curated by our news team.  Weekdays  Grab a quick bite of today's latest news from around the region and the nation.  Weekdays  Catch up on the news of the day and unwind with great reading for your evening.  Weekly  Get the editor's insights: what's happening & why it matters.  Weekly  Going out or staying in? Find out what's on.  Twice weekly  Stay in the know on news that matters to you with twice weekly newsletters from The Senior.  Weekly  Love footy? We have got all the action covered.  Weekly  The latest news, results & expert analysis.  Weekly  Every Saturday and Tuesday, explore destinations 